  <prompt>Extend `infrastructure/bicep/alerts.bicep` (created in task 004) with a NEW scheduled-query log alert that fires when no `RedisKeyRotation` success custom event has been recorded in App Insights for >100 days for any env. Alert query: `customEvents | where name == 'RedisKeyRotation' and customDimensions.outcome == 'success' | summarize last_success = max(timestamp) by tostring(customDimensions.environment)` — fire if any env shows last_success older than 100 days. Use `Microsoft.Insights/scheduledQueryRules`. Route to same on-call action group as the Theme A alerts.</prompt>
  <role>Spaarke infrastructure developer with Bicep + scheduled-query log alerts. Apply `task-execute` skill at STANDARD rigor.</role>
  <goal>alerts.bicep now contains 3 metric alerts (from task 004) + 1 scheduled-query log alert (missed rotation). `az monitor scheduled-query list -g rg-spaarke-dev` will show the rule after task 030 deploy.</goal>
  <context>
    <background>Spec FR-11 — if the automation silently fails (workflow disabled, SP expired, script broken), we need to know within 100 days, not at the next compliance audit.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>infrastructure/bicep/alerts.bicep (EXTEND — created in task 004)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-11 — alert if RedisKeyRotation success custom event missing >100 days for any env.</constraint>
    <constraint source="azure-deployment.md">Idempotent deploy.</constraint>
  </constraints>
